    <!-- Application Structure Plan: Retaining the successful single-page dashboard, the structure is refined for the new context. 1) Header & Summary now frame the goal as finding a SPECIALIST tool to complement the existing NetPositive platform. 2) The "Tool Explorer" cards now include a "Strategic Fit" icon, immediately classifying each tool's role (Specialist, Generalist, etc.). 3) The "Deep Dive Analysis" section is enhanced. The "Overview" tab now has a dedicated "Strategic Role vs. NetPositive" section, which is the most critical new piece of information. This structure allows users to quickly filter for specialists and then dive into a detailed analysis of how they would coexist with current systems. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: Report Info -> 8-tool comparison. Goal -> Compare specialist tools and their fit with existing systems. Viz/Method -> The Radar Chart and tabbed interface are retained for their clarity. The key change is the addition of the "Strategic Role" section within the tabs. Interaction -> Clicking a tool card updates the chart and the tabbed view. Justification -> This explicitly addresses the new context, allowing a user to see not just if a tool is "good," but if it's the "right type of good" for the university's specific needs, avoiding redundancy with NetPositive. Library -> Chart.js. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
