        <section id="summary" class="bg-white p-6 lg:p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm mb-10 md:mb-16 border border-stone-200/80">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-4">Executive Summary</h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-stone-700">
                <p>This analysis evaluates specialist carbon accounting platforms to fill a specific capability gap in the University of Exeter's sustainability toolkit. While the existing **NetPositive Futures** platform is effective for broad sustainability engagement and qualitative reporting, it does not provide the granular, auditable carbon calculation and reduction-modeling features required for a robust Scope 3 decarbonization program. The goal is to identify a tool that excels in this specialist role, avoids supplier-facing costs, and complements NetPositive without creating redundancy or supplier confusion.</p>
                <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800">Based on this focused evaluation, <strong class="text-teal-600">Green Project Tech</strong> and <strong class="text-teal-600">Sweep</strong> are the top recommendations. They are purpose-built carbon specialists whose free-to-supplier models and deep feature sets directly address the university's needs. <strong class="text-teal-600">Greenly</strong> is a strong third contender, while the <strong class="text-amber-600">SCSS Calculator</strong> is identified as an ideal, no-risk tool for an initial pilot.</p>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <section id="tool-explorer" class="mb-10 md:mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2 text-center">Tool Explorer</h2>
            <p class="text-stone-600 mb-8 text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto">Click a tool to analyze its performance as a specialist carbon partner. Pay attention to the "Strategic Fit" icon.</p>
            <div id="tool-grid" class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
