        <footer class="mt-10 md:mt-16 bg-stone-800 text-stone-200 p-8 rounded-2xl">
             <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Conclusion & Next Steps</h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-stone-300">
                <p>The market offers excellent specialist platforms that can integrate with, rather than replace, existing systems. We recommend prioritizing <strong class="text-teal-300">Green Project Tech</strong> and <strong class="text-teal-300">Sweep</strong> for demonstrations due to their clear focus and supplier-friendly models.</p>
                <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-3 mt-4">
                    <li><strong class="text-white">Immediate Action:</strong> Pilot the <strong class="text-amber-300">SCSS Carbon Calculator</strong> with a supplier group to introduce them to quantitative carbon reporting, a perfect complement to their qualitative NetPositive inputs.</li>
                    <li><strong class="text-white">Short-Term Action:</strong> Schedule demos with <strong class="text-teal-300">Green Project Tech</strong>, <strong class="text-teal-300">Sweep</strong>, and <strong class="text-teal-300">Greenly</strong>.</li>
                    <li><strong class="text-white">Crucial Intel:</strong> During demos, focus on interoperability. Ask: <strong class="text-amber-300">"How does your platform complement or integrate with data from broader ESG platforms like NetPositive Futures, which our suppliers already use?"</strong></li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </footer>

